The Vice President of the United States, Mike Pence, delivered a speech at the U.S. Customs and Border Protection headquarters in Washington, D.C. He praised the leadership of Secretary Nielsen and the work of Commissioner McAleenan and Chief Provost. Pence expressed gratitude for the service and sacrifice of the men and women of U.S. Customs and Border Protection and assured them that the administration would provide the necessary resources and reforms to address the humanitarian and security crisis at the southern border. He highlighted the increasing number of families and unaccompanied children attempting to enter the country illegally and emphasized the need for a physical barrier, additional resources, and law reforms. Pence also acknowledged the impact of the partial government shutdown on the families of the federal workers and assured them that efforts were being made to mitigate the impact. He concluded by urging the men and women of U.S. Customs and Border Protection to stay focused on their mission and promised that the administration would support them in securing the border.